DATA CLOUD
Pull Segment Data into Data Cloud for Segment Intelligence

To pull segment data for Segment Intelligence into Data Cloud, create a data stream and map the objects. 

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Available in: Lightning Experience	Available in: Enterprise and Unlimited Editions


USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To manage Data Cloud:	Data Cloud Admin permission set
To set up Segment Intelligence	Data Cloud Admin permission set=
Assign permissions to the users who can create data streams for a segment.
From Setup, in the Quick Find box, enter Permission Sets and then select Permission Sets.
Click Data Cloud Salesforce Connector.
Click Object Settings.
Find and select the Market Segment Definitions object, and click Edit.
Under Object Permissions, select Read and View All, and save your changes.
Click Manage Assignments
Click Add Assignments.
Select the users who can create data streams, and click Assign. 
Click Done.
The selected user can now see the Market Segment object on the Data Stream page in Data Cloud.
Create a data stream to pull in segment data in Data Cloud for Segment Intelligence.
From the App Launcher, find and select Data Cloud.
On the Data Streams tab, click New.
Select Salesforce CRM and click Next.
On the All Objects tab, find and select Segment, and then click Next. 
All the segment fields appear.
Under Object Details, for Category, select Other.
You can edit the field label. For example, you can change Segment Membership data model object name to Segment Membership DMO name.
Click Next.
Select the data space, and click Deploy.
A new data stream is created that pulls in segment data into Data Cloud.
Map the market segment DLO to a DMO.
On the Data Stream tab, click the data stream that you created.
Under Data Mapping, click Start.
Under Data Model entities, click Select Objects.
Under All Objects, find and select Market Segment.
Click the plus icon. The icon changes to a green checkmark.
Click Done.
Map the Segment Name field to Name.
Map the Segment ID field to Market Segment ID.
Click Save and Close.
